<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0913 </DOCNO><TEXT>Now that heating oil is obviously past the point of its lowest price andthat prices for natural gas have been adapted, a comparison of heatingcosts based on realistic assumptions corroborates the competitivenessof natural gas as compared to heating oil both in new and old residentialbuildings. Such competitiveness is underlined by the non-calculable advantagesof natural gas. Given the present relations of prices and costs, thetarget of the German gas industry, which is to convert over 8 millionhouseholds to gas heating by the beginning of the 90s, can be considered,generally speaking, to be absolutely realistic.</TEXT></DOC>